metadata.name: Minima #39
metadata.description:
Minima is a study on focus and color. Playing with the idea of a simple composition of semicircles, either rotated up or down. The focus of the observer is moved with the use of gradual animation in the gradients and occasional circles and/or rectangles connecting the shapes together through color.

The name minima stems from the origins of the composition, mostly taking inspiration from minimalism in its use of a few elements to form a composition greater than the sum of its parts. Less is more, as they say.

The point at the bottom right of the canvas resembles the end of a sentence. Like reading a book, you process the canvas in a similar way, moving from what pops the most to what the least.

As the reader of this canvas I hope you observe what happens to your focus as the colors gradually move across the screen. The animations themselves are looping based on a noised sine wave, which gives them imperfections, imperfections you can observe.

----

Click / Tap on the bar at the bottom of the canvas to open up the GUI, used to export your minima into any format you want. Either .png or .svg. Ready for printing, if you desire.

ps. there might be a secret keyboard shortcut...

----

Minima,
Wouter Missler, 2022,
p5js + webgl.

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #2
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License

metadata.name: Missingno #206
metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing. 
Some call it a bug, very few know what it is truly made of.

Only now with present technology we managed to capture a fraction of its unlimited possible faces.

metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #12
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: The Abstract Truth I  #54
metadata.description:
Moiré patterns meet halftone dots meet cross stitching.

Halftone is a term that can refer to both a technology used in image processing and as the synonym for semitone in music. A jazz musician Oliver Nelson released the album The Blues and the Abstract Truth in 1961. It is considered one of the most significant records of its time. In addition, he wrote Patterns for Improvisation, a hugely popular jazz patterns book. The Moiré pattern design is on the book's cover.

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations. 
Press 'P' to pause/unpause the animation.

metadata.name: Ersbla #373
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.
